System:
Heating-cooling system with radiant panels

System Description:
The IW also uses radiant panels suspended in the ceiling for space heating or cooling. Copper tubing runs along the IW ceiling and is in direct contact with aluminium panel modules to conduct heat. The aluminium panel modules then act as the radiator. Depending on the indoor setpoint temperature and seasonal needs, the system can be turned on or off.

System Parts & Installation Dates:

  • TACO Incorporated 0011-F4 pump (1997)
  • Siemens SSA61U actuator valve (March 2011)
  • Setra 206/207 pressure transducers (March 2011)
